"{\"uid\": \"telecomasia.net-news-other-simone-biles-does-not-rule-out-her-participation-in-2028-summer-olympics-at-home\", \"text\": \"American gymnast Simone Biles, a 23-time world champion and record holder, spoke to USA Today and allowed her participation in the 2028 Summer Olympics to be held in Los Angeles.  The 27-year-old Biles stated:  On August 3, the American celebrated success in the vault competition at the 2024 Games in Paris, receiving a score of 15.300 from the judges. Also Biles became the best in the individual all-around competition, and also won first place with the national team in the French capital.  Thus, the gymnast became a seven-time Olympic champion. The record holder is nine-time Olympic champion (1956, 1960, 1964), Soviet athlete Larisa Latynina.  All materials on this site are available under licenseCreative Commons Attribution 4.0 International. You must include the name of the author (creator) of the work (material) and the party of attribution, copyright notice, license title, disclaimer notice and link to the material, if provided with the material.\"}"